The Commander 17 Brigade Nigerian Army Katsina State, Brigadier General Ibikunle Ajose, has assured corps members in the state of adequate security in and outside the orientation camp. Ajose gave the assurance on Friday when he paid a surprise visit to the NYSC Orientation Camp. The 17 Brigade Commander was conducted round the camp facilities by the NYSC State Coordinator, Alhaji Ahidjo Yahaya, who received him on arrival to the camp ground. Speaking on the essence of his visit, Ajose said he was at the camp to ascertain the level of security in and around the corps members and other camp operators, noting that “the comfort and safety of the corps members undergoing the orientation course is top-most in his priorities.” While assuring the authority of adequate security for corps members in and outside the orientation camp, General Ajose promised to sponsor the finals of the football and volleyball tournaments in the ongoing inter-platoon sports competitions as well as provide a fat cow for the corps members camp night scheduled towards the tail end of the orientation camp.